divs: Sighting Details Brightlight came from right to left(east to west) horizon to horizon in less than fiveseconds. Then made a ninety degree turn to the south and stopped behind a puffycumulus cloud( one of two small cumulus clouds on the left of the vehicle.) Itthen jumped behind the other cumulus cloud for a few seconds. I saw enough ofthe object to see the curvature of the white light, but not the entire object. It was sort of arrowhead shaped. Witness works for Defense Electronic supplyCenter in Dayton,OH and is familiar with aircraft. The maneuvers of this objectand speed were not a conventional aircraft.
